subSubSection.paragraph:
Head
(
Figs 9A–D
). Rostrum in males (
Fig. 9B
) distinctly tapered in basal half and enlarged in apical half, with concave sides and subparallel-sided in females (
Fig. 9C
), slightly tapered in basal half and indistinctly enlarged in apical half, rounded around scrobes, in males 1.09–1.12× as wide as long, at apex as wide as at base; in females 1.16–1.25× as wide as long, at base 1.04–1.09× as wide as at apex, in both sexes distinctly narrower than head including eyes. Epifrons with slender longitudinal median stria, when cleared of scales shiny, shallowly deepened with several fine punctures, with short slender longitudinal median stria on basal half and with two very slender subparallel keels along whole length. Frons deepened, finely rough. Epistome in males wide, wider than epifrons at midlength, in females narrow, equally wide as epifrons at midlength. Head when cleared of scales shiny, distinctly convex, with small fovea and slender median longitudinal stria on apical half, with only several very slender and short striae and punctures mainly on anterior part and along eyes. Eyes weakly prominent from outline of head.
